turns.speaker: M
turns.content: [LAUGHTER]

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: [LAUGHTER] Utterly, utterly ridiculous.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: We were very much younger then.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Very much sillier.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Mmhmm.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: However, I do believe the real cause of that row was Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh you knew there was nothing in that.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I knew nothing of the sort. You took presents from him.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Presents? It was a trivial little broach.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It was bristling with diamonds in the worst possible taste.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not at all. It was very pretty. I still wear it often.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You sent out of your way to torture me over Peter Burden.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I did not you worked whole thing up in your jealous imagination.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, you let him kiss you.  You said you did.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well, what of it?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What of it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It gave him a lot, a great deal of pleasure and it didn't hurt me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: And what about me?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: If you hadn't been so suspicious and nosey you'd never known a thing about it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That's a nice point of view I must say.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I'm bored with this conversation.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: So am I.  I'm bored stiff.  You want some brandy?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, thank you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'll have a little, I think.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't see why you want any you already had two glasses.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh, you know no particular reason besides they are very small glasses.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I just think it's silly you know to go on and on and on about such a thing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You can hardly call three glasses of liquor in a whole evening going on and on and on.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I just, I just think it's becoming a habit with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Hmm.  Well, you needn't be so grand just because you don't happen to want any at the moment, okay?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Do be quiet.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Really, Amanda.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Don't be stupid, what?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Nothing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Are you going out somewhere dear?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No, darling I'm just making myself fascinating for you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That reply has broken my heart.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well it's a woman's duty to allure the man. Watch me a minute will you?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: As matter the fact that's perfectly true.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh no, it isn't.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes, it is.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Don't be stupid, shut up.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You know, it's a pity you didn't have any more brandy. It would have made you just a little less disagreeable.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, well that's funny.  It doesn't seem to have worked such wonders with you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You know what?  You snap, you snap, you snap you're like a little adder.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Adders don't snap, they sting.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Nonsense.  They have a bag of venom behind of fangs and they snap.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They sting.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I don't care.  I don't care, do you understand?  I don't mind if they bark and they roll about like hoops.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Did you see much of Peter Burden after our divorce?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yes, I did quite a lot.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I suppose you let him just kiss you or good deal more than too.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, mind you own business.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I suppose you two had a riotous time, huh?  No restrain at all, very enjoyable, he never had much any how.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're quite insufferable, I expect it's because you're drunk.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I am not in the least bit drunk.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You always had a weak head.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I think I told you once before that I had three minute liquor glasses the whole evening long.  A Child of two cannot get drunk on that.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: On the contrary, a child two could get violently drunk on only one glass of brandy.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Oh very, very interesting Amanda.  How about the child of uh... four, six or maybe nine---you know, we could work up a splendid little debate about it, you know?  Intemperate tots.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Shut up.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not very funny darling.  Why don't you have some more brandy?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That's a very good idea I think I will.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Would you uh...turn that off please? You're going to wake the people upstairs.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: There are no people upstairs. It's a photographer's studio.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well then you'll wake the people downstairs.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: They are away in Tunis.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: This is no time a year for Tunis.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Turn it on again, please.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I will do no such thing.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Very well if you insist on being boorish and idiotic.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off. It's driving me mad.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I won't.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Turn it off.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Stop it. No. Go away.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Amanda listen. Listen.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: listen Oh I'm sick and tired of listening to you, you damn sadistic bully.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: That's very amusing indeed.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh you're cruel you're...you're...I hate you, I hate you. Go away. You're conceited. You're overbearing. You're utterly impossible.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You...You're an evil minded, self-centered little wench and I never want to see you again.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: This is the end do you hear me?  Finally and forever.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're not going like this.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh yes I am...Oh yes I am. Let go of me. You let go. You...urgh...You're a cruel friend. I loathe and I hate you. Marry you again...Ha...Never, never, never, never. I hope you die in torment. You beast.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No you're not.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Shut up. Shut up. I wouldn't marry you again if you came crawling back to me on a bended knee. You are an evil tempered little vampire and I never want to see you again as long as I live.
